Shanghai Awards Research Achievements 
Shanghai, China's largest commercial center, has awarded 1.2 million
yuan in prizes to local scientists responsible for 275 research
achievements.
The bulk of the achievements were recorded in applied hi-tech projects
and basic scientific research. For example, a new computer system will
ensure wireless telecommunications departments with access to abundant
power sources.
In addition, medical researchers working at Fudan University and
Changhai Hospital in the city developed effective medical treatment for
four hemophiliacs.
